To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

All releasable documents concerning the Request for Proposals with  PIN # 61540003 (advertised in the City Record as a procurement for a "NYC Ferry service operator")

This may include the following:
• The RFP itself, including any revisions;
• Materials prepared for the evaluation of proposals;
• Materials provided at the information sessions and site visits for prospective proposers;
• List of event attendees and plan-holders;
• Proposals, including any mandatory disclosures;
• Any exchange of questions and answers that is part of the RFP process. 

Should procurement rules or state law require the agency to deny this request in part, the agency should release the remaining portions in a manner consistent with the New York Freedom of Information Law.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

T. McElwee
